<section class="faq-section" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
  <div style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px">
    <h2 id="faq-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <p class="faq-sub">Common questions jewellers ask before choosing a billing & ERP partner.</p>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How does the system update gold rate automatically?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Our jewellery ERP polls live bullion-rate feeds (BSE/MCX-linked supplier APIs or your trusted bullion dealer's webhook) at intervals you set — typically every 15 to 60 minutes. The new rate flows into the billing screen, item master valuation, and approval-voucher revaluation. Branch managers can override with a four-eye approval, and every rate change is logged for audit.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Does it support BIS hallmark and HUID tracking?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Each piece is tagged with its 6-character HUID, BIS hallmark centre code, purity (14k/18k/22k), and assay date. The HUID is printed on the tax invoice and is searchable for warranty, repair, and buy-back. Bulk HUID import from the BIS Hallmark portal is supported, and the system blocks billing of any item without a valid HUID for hallmarked categories.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can RFID auto-take stock without scanning each item?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. With UHF RFID tags on every piece, a handheld or fixed reader scans an entire tray, drawer, or showcase in seconds. The ERP reconciles the read list against the system's expected stock and flags missing, mis-located, or unauthorised pieces. A 5,000-piece showroom audit that used to take a full day drops to under 30 minutes.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How does old-gold exchange work in the software?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">The exchange screen captures gross weight, purity (carat/touch from XRF or stone test), stone weight to deduct, and computes net pure-gold value at the day's rate minus your wastage and melt-loss policy. The customer's adjustment voucher posts directly against the new sale invoice, and a bullion-account journal records the inward fine gold. Full audit trail with photos of the old item is stored.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Does it handle karigar (artisan) job-work?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. The karigar module issues raw gold/silver weight against a job order, tracks design and expected weight, and on receipt records final weight, stones added, wastage absorbed, and labour due. Karigar-wise wastage % trends, ageing of issued metal, and outstanding bullion balances are visible on a single dashboard — solving the biggest leakage point in manufacturing jewellery.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Is e-invoicing supported for B2B jewellery sales?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. For B2B invoices above the GST e-invoicing threshold, the ERP generates IRN through GSP/IRP integration, prints the QR code on the tax invoice, creates the e-way bill where applicable, and pushes data to GSTR-1. Multi-GSTIN setups for jewellers with branches in Tamil Nadu, Karnataka, Kerala, and beyond are fully supported.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can it integrate with our existing showroom hardware (RFID readers, barcode printers)?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. We integrate with mainstream UHF RFID readers (handheld and fixed-portal), thermal jewellery tag printers, weighing scales with serial/USB output, XRF purity testers, customer-display poles, and cash drawers. If you already own hardware, share the make and model and we will build the driver shim — no need to replace working equipment.</div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

